A 16-year-old girl has following a horror crash in a residential area. The teenager died at the scene, police confirmed today, after to cars collided in Oldham, Greater Manchester, at around 1.30pm.   A man has been arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving, police said. One of the vehicles mounted the pavement and collided with the teenager, who was a pedestrian. Emergency services rushed to the scene but despite the best efforts of paramedics, the girl was sadly pronounced dead at the scene. The man, who is in his 20s, was arrested at the scene, reports the Manchester Evening News. He currently remains in custody waiting to be quizzed by detectives. The case has been referred to GMP's Serious Collision Investigation Unit.   The street in question - Rochdale Road - was closed for a number of hours on Thursday afternoon as officers and detectives carried out their investigations at the scene of the smash. Pictures from the scene showed a large number of police and emergency services in attendance. A damaged black vehicle was visible within the cordon. Police are appealing for anyone who may have witnessed the incident, or who may have dashcam footage or doorbell footage to come forward.  You can do so by calling 0161 856 4741 quoting incident number 1677 of 23/2/2023. You can also make a report via the website www.gmp.police.uk. Alternatively, information can be shared anonymously via the independent charity Crimestoppers on 0800 555 111. Tributes were shared on Facebook and other social media sites. "RIP poor girl," one Facebook user posted today. Another posted: "Such terrible, heartbreaking news. RIP youngster and thoughts go to your family at this time." A third simply posted: "Awful news, rest in peace." 